commit.message: fix changed dh structure in openssl 3. Change include order so that we can set compatibility symbols in the generated code

Allow NRPE to compile on EL 9/Debian 11/Ubuntu 22 (maybe).

Still needs more thorough testing - wrote a short program that generates the same code that
would have been created by `openssl dhparam -C` by reading output from `openssl dhparam -text`.
We also set OPENSSL_API_COMPAT to version 1.1.1 and set OPENSSL_NO_DEPRECATED so that compile warnings are suppressed.

Use sockaddr_storage instead of sockaddr

This fixes the call of getpeername() and prevents an out-of-bound read.

load intermediate cert from certfile

This is required for public certificates as many servers will be unable to verify the certificate if a partial chain is presented.
Changing `SSL_CTX_use_certificate_file` to `SSL_CTX_use_certificate_chain_file` fixes this issue since now the certificate and intermediate can be loaded from the same file.
This reflects behaviour of other software including popular webservers.
Furthermore the use of `SSL_CTX_use_certificate_chain_file` is suggested by the corresponding OpenSSL man page.

Signed-off-by: benaryorg <binary@benary.org>

load intermediate cert from certfile

This is required for public certificates as many servers will be unable to verify the certificate if a partial chain is presented.
Changing `SSL_CTX_use_certificate_file` to `SSL_CTX_use_certificate_chain_file` fixes this issue since now the certificate and intermediate can be loaded from the same file.
This reflects behaviour of other software including popular webservers.
Furthermore the use of `SSL_CTX_use_certificate_chain_file` is suggested by the corresponding OpenSSL man page.

Signed-off-by: benaryorg <binary@benary.org>

commit.message: Fix compilation in seperate build directory.
Enforce server cipher order and disable renegotiation if available.
Use correct format for size_t result from sizeof().

Fix SSL certificate handling.

Always load CA certificates if available.

Use SSL_CTX_use_certificate_chain_file() to load our public certifcate
to allow loading intermediate & root CAs.

Verify that certificate & private key match.

This allows us to present the full certificate chain during handshake
with the intermediate & root CAs stored in either the CA file or
certificate file or a combination thereof.
Fix code block formatting

commit.message:
Patch to allow passing --enable-tcpd or --disable-tcpd.

If passing --enable-tcpd and libwrap is not available, ./configure will
fail.

If passing --disable-tcpd, libwrap will be completely ignore.

If not passed, current behaviour still applies.

Signed-off-by: Jaco Kroon <jaco@iewc.co.za>
Adding ppc64le architecture support on travis-ci
Fix option is --use-adh, not --use-dh in usage()

Return UNKNOWN instead of CRITICAL on all SSL-layer problems

Plugin should behave consistently and report CRITICAL only when explicitly got from
remote side or remote side is completely down.

All other cases, when remote side is up, but we unable to get correct response - should
return UNKNOWN, like it was implemented for non-SSL connections.
